Class LexFile

java.lang.Object
  edu.mit.jwi.item.LexFile
All Implemented Interfaces:
IHasPOS, ILexFile
Direct Known Subclasses:
UnknownLexFile
public class LexFile
extends java.lang.Object
implements ILexFile

Concrete implementation of the ILexFile interface. This class in not implemented as an enum so that clients may instantiate their own LexFile objects using this implementation.

Since:
1.5.0
Version:
2.1.5, Jan 10, 2008
Author:
Mark A. Finlayson

Checks the specified lexical file number to see if it is a valid lexical file number. If not, throws an exception.

isIllegalLexicalFileNumber

public static boolean isIllegalLexicalFileNumber(int lexFileNum)
A lexical file number is always in the closed range [0, 99]. In the wordnet data files, it is represented as a two digit decimal integer.

Returns:
true if the number is an illegal lexical file number; false otherwise.

getLexicalFileNumberString

public static java.lang.String getLexicalFileNumberString(int lexFileNum)
A lexical file number is always in the closed range [0, 99]. In the wordnet data files, it is represented as a two digit decimal integer. This method returns a two-character, zero-filled decimal digit string representing the

Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the specified integer is not a legal lexical file number
